_printf - main function

flag - stuct for storing flags
formats - store a character and a matching format function
finit - initializer for flag stuct
sinit - initialize a string to ' ' and terminate

dflags - detect flags from given string and update a flag struct, returning new string position
dwidth - detect width in given string and save to flag struct, returning new string pos
dper - detect the . marker and save the following number to flag struct

lstrgen - allocate space for a string based on length and  fill with main str
fstrlen - get the length of a string, and change based on per flag
inttostr - convert and int to a string, saving the '-' 
revstr - reverse a section of a string

specifier - execute the apropriate fuction given a string and position, and pass flag struct and va_arg
prntchar - print a single given char and return number of printed character
prntc - print a singe char formated with flags and widt and return number of printed characterh
prnts - print a string with width and flag and return number of printed characters
prntd - print an signed int with flag and return printed characters
prntund - handle printing of an undifined specifier
